ITSM Project Summary
====================

Overview
- Internal ITSM platform providing ticketing, assets, users, suppliers, admin configuration, mail integration, workflows, SLA tracking, escalation, approvals, and reporting.
- Frontend: React (Vite), TypeScript.
- Backend: Node/Express with Postgres.

How It Works (High Level)
1. Users create tickets via UI or inbound mail.
2. Tickets are assigned to queues based on team and routing rules.
3. Agents accept tickets to take ownership.
4. Agents work tickets using notes, emails, and escalation.
5. Status is controlled by workflow transitions.
6. SLA is tracked for response and resolution targets.
7. Tickets close after resolution.

Primary Navigation
- Dashboard
- Tickets
- Assets
- Users
- Suppliers
- Reports
- Accounts
- Admin


Tickets Module (How It Works)
- Ticket creation
  - From New Ticket button or inbound email.
  - Required fields: Type, Subject, Description.
  - Ticket ID generated as TB#00001 format.
- Queue placement
  - Tickets appear under team queues in the left panel.
  - Unassigned queue contains tickets without staff assignment.
- Acceptance
  - Accept Ticket assigns to the logged agent.
  - Accept action appears in timeline with logged user name.
- Actions and updates
  - Email User: sends outbound email to requester.
  - Log to Supplier: links and logs to supplier channel.
  - Internal note: visible only to agents.
  - Private note: personal log if enabled.
  - Note + Email: internal log plus outbound email.
- Status handling
  - Status updates follow workflow transitions.
  - Invalid transitions are blocked with error message.
  - Status badge reflects current state in ticket info panel.
- Conversation views
  - All Conversation shows full system and user/agent updates.
  - Conversation & Internal hides system progress updates.
- Escalation
  - Target team and optional staff selection.
  - Staff dropdown is filtered by selected team membership.
  - Unassigned is supported (null assignee).
  - Ticket moves to new queue and appears under new team.
- Updates from end users
  - Inbound mail reply marks list badge as �Update� (orange) but does not change actual status.

SLA & Priorities (How It Works)
- SLA timer starts based on ticket priority.
- Response SLA stops when agent uses Mark as responsed.
- Resolution SLA continues until ticket is closed.
- Green tick means SLA met; red X means breached.

Mail Configuration (How It Works)
- Supports Gmail, Outlook, Zoho, Custom SMTP/IMAP per mailbox.
- Per-mailbox configuration includes IMAP/SMTP or OAuth.
- Default IMAP/SMTP values auto-filled for common providers.
- Auto-route rebuild occurs when new mailbox is added or migrated.
- Outbound emails only sent when agent/admin explicitly uses ticket mail actions.

Email Templates & Signatures (How It Works)
- Templates support placeholders like $ticketID$, $subject$, $User Name$.
- Used by Email User and Note + Email actions.
- Signatures can be configured per agent or globally.

Assets Module (How It Works)
- Asset creation includes identification, assignment, and details fields.
- Details tab is visible only for Laptop, Workstation, Desktop, PC.
- Assets can be linked to tickets and users.

Asset Types & Fields (How It Works)
- Categories act as parents (Hardware, Software, Cloud).
- Asset Types are children under categories.
- Only child types appear in asset selection dropdown.

Users & Agents (How It Works)
- Agents and Users are separate records.
- Adding an agent does not create a user entry.
- Users table holds employee info (work email, department, reporting manager, employee ID, employment type, work mode).
- Duplicate user creation should be blocked by work email.

Suppliers (How It Works)
- Suppliers list contains vendor contacts.
- Supplier selected during Log to Supplier action.
- Supplier email auto-fills based on supplier record.

Admin Settings (How It Works)
- Queue Management: manage queues, team visibility, and default routing.
- Workflow: control allowed status transitions per ticket type.
- Mail Configuration: provider setup and routing for inbound/outbound.
- Templates: define email and signature content.
- Security: login policies, session timeout, IP restrictions, SSO.

UI/UX Consistency
- Unified avatar + presence dot for logged user across queue list, profile, and timeline cards.
- Background panels and toolbars are styled consistently across admin sections.

Reports
- Reports panel is currently empty; can be develop later.

Accounts
- Accounts is currently empty; can be develop later.

Database & IDs
- Ticket IDs use TB#00001 format.
- Reset operations can restart numbering when required.

Known Considerations
- Workflow rules are authoritative for status changes; update workflow to allow valid transitions.
- Escalation should never assign staff outside selected team.
- Duplicate user creation must be prevented using work email.

Build/Deployment
- Frontend build: `npm run build` or `npx vite build`.
- Backend and frontend can be restarted independently.
- Git workflow on main branch as requested.

End of Summary
